Carrier pre-selection has been introduced in Mauritius since 1 January 2005. The international prefix “00” may be used only by those subscribers who have pre-selected an International Long Distance (ILD) carrier. For subscribers who have not pre-selected any carrier, their international calls made using the prefix “00” are not allowed through.All subscribers may however select the ILD carrier of their choice on a Call-by-Call basis by using the carrier prefix assigned to the selected carrier, by the ICTA (ILD Carrier Prefix: 020, 022, 030, 033, 040, 050, 060, 070).
